   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1832_07_22_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>
                  <date when="1816-08-04"/>July 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1832</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>My very dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockS1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Lockhart</persName>. I have not<lb/>
                        written to you or <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lockhart</persName> because I<lb/>
                        felt so truly for you and knew how odious<lb/>
                        it must be to you to receive and answer<lb/>
                        inquiries - I see by the last newspaper<lb/>
                        that you have arrived at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Abbotsford-House_STK">Abbotsford</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I am glad that point which must be so<lb/>
                    near your heart since it was so much<lb/>
                    his wish has been attained - I hope that<lb/>
                    the account is true that he is better? - that<lb/>
                    the sight of home and the being once more<lb/>
                    in his library has been reviving? While<lb/>
                    I ask - I almost fear upon such an <choice>
                  <orig>un-<lb/>
                        certainty</orig>
                  <reg>uncertainty</reg>
               </choice> hasarding the giving you so much<lb/>
                    pain - if this should be a mistaken statement<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>   Having loved a father - and having
                         known <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">your father</persName> &amp; seen you with him<lb/>
                         I can &amp; do feel for you and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Lock<lb/>
                             hart</orig>
                     <reg>Lockhart</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>of whose attachment to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">Sir Walter Scott</persName>
               <lb/>
                         seen in the happy hours we travelled <choice>
                  <orig>toge<lb/>
                             ther</orig>
                  <reg>together</reg>
               </choice>, I have the deepest remembrance<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>   If you <hi rend="underline">can</hi> do pray one of you write a<lb/>
                    line <add>to me</add> - if you have any thing good to say - if not<lb/>
                    do not give yourselves the pain - Remember me<lb/>
                    affectionately to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotA1">Miss Scott</persName>. &amp; if you write tell me<lb/>
                    how she does - <lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    Believe me most sincerely
                    your <unclear>grateful</unclear> friend
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
